For a relation given as a set of ordered pairs (x, y):

• The domain consists of all distinct x-values (first coordinates).  
• The range consists of all distinct y-values (second coordinates).

Given relation  
{ (−3, 7), (−2, 3), (−1, 9), (0, −3), (−1, 8) }

a) Domain  
Extract the first coordinate from each pair and list each value once:
{ −3, −2, −1, 0 }

b) Range  
Extract the second coordinate from each pair and list each value once:
{ 7, 3, 9, −3, 8 }

So,  
Domain = {−3, −2, −1, 0}  
Range = {7, 3, 9, −3, 8}

